   dereference this invalid memory address, leading to a segmentation fault.
   
   ROOT CAUSE: program.cpp:11: The program performs pointer arithmetic on a
   heap-allocated pointer (`n--`) before calling `delete`, which passes an
   incorrect address to the deallocator (causing heap corruption/undefined
   behavior) and leaves `n` as a dangling pointer.
   
   LOCAL FIX: Remove the pointer decrement `n--` before the `delete` operation.
